     "text": [
      "Ahoy, matey! To check if a Python object be an instance of a class, ye can use the `isinstance()` function. Here’s how ye can do it:\n",
      "\n",
      "```python\n",
      "class Ship:\n",
      "    pass\n",
      "\n",
      "my_ship = Ship()\n",
      "\n",
      "# Check if my_ship be an instance of Ship\n",
      "if isinstance(my_ship, Ship):\n",
      "    print(\"Aye, she be a ship!\")\n",
      "else:\n",
      "    print(\"Nay, she be not a ship!\")\n",
      "```\n",
      "\n",
      "This here `isinstance()` function takes two arguments: the object ye be checkin' (`my_ship` in this case) and the class ye be comparin' it to (`Ship`). If the object be an instance of that class, it returns `True`. If not, it returns `False! Arrr!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
